nic turbulence. We find that\nthe power spectrum P(rho^(1/3)v) scales with wavenumber as k^(-1.74) for\nsolenoidal driving, close to incompressible Kolmogorov turbulence, k^(-5/3),\nbut is significantly steeper with k^(-2.10) for compressive driving. We show\nthat this is consistent with a recent theoretical model for compressible\nturbulence that predicts P(rho^(1/3)v) k^(-19/9) in the presence of a strong\ndiv(v) component as is produced by compressive driving and remains remarkably\nconstant throughout the supersonic turbulent cascade.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 17 Jun 2013 20:00:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 5 Aug 2013 03:19:08 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 2 Sep 2013 04:44:57 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 24 Sep 2013 16:36:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-09-25"}
